Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.93,0:01:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0008,,{\fn华文楷体\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&\blur3}宇宙:宇宙现象{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.71,0:00:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}创世之初 冥冥之中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the beginning, there was darkness...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.23,0:00:06.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}随着轰的一声{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and then, bang...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.37,0:00:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}诞生了无限膨胀的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}giving birth to an endless expanding existence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.60,0:00:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}时间 空间和物质{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of time, space, and matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.20,0:00:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}现在 所见超乎我们的想象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Now, see further than we've ever imagined...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.93,0:00:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}超越了我们生存的限制{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}beyond the limits of our existence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.90,0:00:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这个空间我们称之为"宇宙"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in a place we call "The Universe."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.99,0:00:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳风 宇宙射线 紫外线辐射{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Solar wind, cosmic rays, and UV radiation.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.09,0:00:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们都是来自外太空的力量 影响着我们的日常生活{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They're forces from outer space that affect our lives every day...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.84,0:00:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们大多数人甚至还不知道它{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and most of us don't even know it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.14,0:00:43.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从皮肤癌到通讯中断{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}From skin cancer to lost transmissions...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.67,0:00:47.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些宇宙现象会给我们带来伤害{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}these cosmic phenomena can cause us harm...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.33,0:00:54.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是它们也会给我们带来绚丽夺目的极光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}yet they can also dazzle us with the beauty of an aurora...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.36,0:00:57.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}和灿烂的流星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the brilliance of a shooting star.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.80,0:01:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}敬请收看集奇观与危害于一身的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Get ready for the wonders and the dangers...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.91,0:01:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}《宇宙现象》{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of "Cosmic Phenomena."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.64,0:01:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它恢宏壮观{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's just magnificent.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.08,0:01:29.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它变幻莫测{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's full of dynamic motion.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.55,0:01:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们看到它千变万化{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It is changing every time we look at it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.78,0:01:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它是你所见到的最大的东西{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's the biggest thing you have ever seen.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.43,0:01:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它是美轮美奂的景色{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's just a beautiful sight...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.03,0:01:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}好像全然不同于我们所知的一切{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}kind of completely unlike anything we know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.47,0:01:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}简直不可思议 空中居然有这样的表现{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's so weird to see the sky behaving in such a fashion.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.38,0:01:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你看到天上这些闪烁的光辉{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You see these flittering lights in the sky...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.44,0:01:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们千变万化 绚丽多彩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and they're changing with time in beautiful and wondrous ways.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.51,0:01:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}真是恍若世外{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's really an out-of-this-world experience.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.25,0:02:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}人的一生{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Once in everyone's lifetime...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.80,0:02:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}应该去看一回最壮观的景象之一{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they should see one of the most spectacular...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.82,0:02:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}魔幻般的光彩表现出大自然的慷慨{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}psychedelic light shows that nature gives us...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.43,0:02:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那就是北极光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and that's the aurora borealis.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.58,0:02:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其名字来自奥罗拉(曙光) 罗马曙光女神{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It was named after Aurora, the Roman goddess of dawn...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.73,0:02:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}和希腊北风之神 玻瑞阿斯{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the Greek god of the north wind, Boreas.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.10,0:02:22.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在南半球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the southern hemisphere...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.73,0:02:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它被称为南极光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it's known as the aurora australis.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.52,0:02:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们长期困惑着天文学家{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Way before they dazzled astronomers...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.82,0:02:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极光震撼了第一个在极地见到它的人{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}auroras amazed the first people who saw them in the polar regions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.15,0:02:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}惟有古斯堪的纳维亚人{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}To ancient Scandinavians...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.70,0:02:41.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}会对这眼花缭乱的展现作出同样惊人的解释{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}only an equally amazing explanation for the dazzling displays would do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.62,0:02:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}他们相信天上有一只大狐狸 甩动着尾巴{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They believed a giant fox in the sky, swooshing its tail...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.61,0:02:49.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}导致了北极光的出现{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}caused the northern lights to appear.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.38,0:02:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我喜欢这个解释{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}I like that explanation...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.64,0:02:56.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为它并非不切实际{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because it is not that far from the truth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.04,0:02:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极光是一种电现象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The aurora is an electric phenomena.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.84,0:03:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在狐狸甩动尾巴时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And when a fox swooshes its tail around...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.03,0:03:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你在和静电打交道{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}you deal with static electricity...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.87,0:03:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你可能实际上产生了火花 类似极光的现象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and you may actually make sparks and an aurora-like phenomenon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.98,0:03:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果你想知道极光是怎么来的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}lf you want to know how an aurora comes about...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.88,0:03:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就必须从太阳说起{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}you have to start at the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.16,0:03:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.76,0:03:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它不光是光源 而且还是能源 大量的能源{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's not only our source of light, but also energy, lots of it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.85,0:03:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳发出源源不断的带电粒子流{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Sun emits a steady stream of charged particles...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.79,0:03:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}叫做太阳风{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}known as solar wind...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.48,0:03:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有时会被日冕物质抛射加剧的宇宙力量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}a cosmic force sometimes intensified by a coronal mass ejection.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.94,0:03:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳风会导致大气层上部的辉光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Solar wind can cause some glow in the upper atmosphere...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.71,0:03:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}几乎全年任何时候{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}nearly any time of the year.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.73,0:03:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不过 偶尔 太阳会有这些巨大的爆发{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But, occasionally, the Sun has these tremendous outbursts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.21,0:03:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们被称为太阳耀斑或日冕物质抛射{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They're called solar flares or coronal mass ejections.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.11,0:03:54.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}于是整个带电粒子流{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And then a whole stream of charged particles...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.21,0:03:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}差不多同时奔向地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}comes to the Earth at about the same time...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.06,0:03:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}一大团 一大团{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}a whole bundle, a whole bunch of them.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.99,0:04:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那便产生了大量炫丽的极光现象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And that then causes a lot brighter auroral phenomena.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.84,0:04:09.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}速度高达每秒750英里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Traveling at speeds of up to 750 miles per second...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.08,0:04:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}使得太阳风在两天左右就抵达地球的磁场{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it takes solar wind about two days to reach the Earth's magnetic field.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.99,0:04:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}随着带电粒子...{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As the energized particles...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.71,0:04:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}沿着磁场流向两极...{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}stream along the magnetic field towards the poles...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.90,0:04:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们激发了地球大气层上部的气体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they excite gases on the Earth's upper atmosphere...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.88,0:04:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}产生出彩光 形成了极光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and produce the colored lights that make up the aurora.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.75,0:04:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}高能粒子轰击大气层上部{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When the energetic particles hit the upper atmosphere...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.73,0:04:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}首先遇上氧原子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they first encounter atomic oxygen...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.50,0:04:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}给我们带来红光谱射线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which gives us the red line emission...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.85,0:04:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}绿光谱射线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the green line emission...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.03,0:04:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极光中最普遍的射线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the most prevalent emission in aurora.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.09,0:04:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}往下 你会遇上氮分子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Further down, you can encounter molecular nitrogen...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.11,0:04:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那就给我们 要是极光非常剧烈的话{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and that gives us, if the aurora's very intense...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.00,0:04:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在绿帷幕的底部边缘{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}at the bottom edge of the green curtain...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:51.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有紫色的下摆{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}a purple lower border.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.19,0:04:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}带电粒子与敏感气体相互作用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Charged particles interacting with excitable gases...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.42,0:05:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}产生出明亮的光彩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to produce bright colors...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.08,0:05:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极光的活动极像霓虹灯{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the aurora functions much like a neon sign.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.21,0:05:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}霓虹灯的原理 如果你取上少许稀有气体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Neon works by-- If you take a little bit of a rare gas...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.24,0:05:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}放入压力极小的管子里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and put it in a tube at very low pressure...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.67,0:05:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}然后你通电 随便从3000V 或4000V{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and then you apply anywhere from 3,000 or 4,000 volts...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.61,0:05:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}或者1.5万V 电离气体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to maybe 15,000 volts will ionize the gas...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.59,0:05:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}激发它发出其特有的色彩{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and excite it into giving off its characteristic color.{\r}
