Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.16,0:10:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳的一举一动 当它的外层大气发生变化时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}What the Sun does, when it varies the outer atmosphere...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.85,0:10:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就会影响到地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it affects the Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.20,0:10:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此它影响到系统{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So it affects the systems...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.41,0:10:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们所依赖的技术系统{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the technological systems that we depend on.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.52,0:10:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}尽管极光只是...{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Though auroras are a mere side effect...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.70,0:10:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳与地球互动的副作用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of the Sun's interaction with the Earth...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.56,0:10:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是它们可以启发我们对宇宙的认识{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they can enlighten us about the cosmos.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.26,0:10:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极光是个很好的指示 有关大气层上部的情况{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The aurora is a good indicator of how the upper atmosphere...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.66,0:10:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}以及地球磁场与最终来自太阳的...{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the magnetic field of the Earth interact with the solar wind...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.77,0:10:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳风的相互作用{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which eventually comes from the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.54,0:10:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此我们可以将极光作为研究对象 本质上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So we can use the aurora as a study object, essentially...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.99,0:11:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大自然让我们去更好地了解{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that nature provides for us to understand better...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.67,0:11:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙其它地方所发生的情况{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}what goes on in the rest of the universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.95,0:11:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极光是太阳活动的度量之一{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The auroras are one of the measures of solar activity.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.55,0:11:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此在历史的回顾中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So in tracing history back from the present day...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.40,0:11:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}追溯到10世纪 或8世纪乃至更早{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}back to the 10th century or the 8th century or even before...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.63,0:11:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极光就是你可以用作...{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the auroras are one thing that you can use...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.35,0:11:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}衡量太阳的活动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}as a measure of solar activity.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.78,0:11:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳有个22年的活动周期{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So the Sun has a 22-year cycle of activity.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.63,0:11:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}每11年 它会变得比较活跃{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Every 11 years, it becomes more active...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.48,0:11:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而且它还颠倒了极性 颠了个倒{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and then it reverses its polarity and comes back.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.16,0:11:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}然而你可以通过时间来追溯{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But you can trace this back in time...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.67,0:11:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极光就是那最好的标志{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the auroras are one of the best markers of that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.70,0:11:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}虽然极光最常见到是在极地{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}While auroras are most often viewed in the polar regions...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.64,0:11:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是其它闪亮耀眼的宇宙现象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there are other dazzling cosmic phenomena...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.28,0:11:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是所有地方都能见到的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that can be seen anywhere.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们叫做流星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They're called shooting stars.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.36,0:11:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们看到的流星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When we see shooting stars...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.33,0:11:48.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}看上去好像恒星落向了地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they look like stars that fell onto the planet Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.43,0:11:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但不是那回事{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But that can't be right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.77,0:11:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}恒星比地球大多了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Stars are much bigger than the planet Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.16,0:11:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果你真的看到有一颗流星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If you really had a shooting star...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.76,0:11:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那它会在一秒钟内吞噬掉地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it would gobble up the Earth within a fraction of a second.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.66,0:12:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此如果它不是恒星 那又是什么呢?{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So if it's not a star, then what is it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.07,0:12:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那只是个小石子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's just a little, tiny pebble...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.75,0:12:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}比如来自外太空的一粒沙子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}like a grain of sand from outer space...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.10,0:12:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}划过我们的大气层{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}zipping through our atmosphere...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.11,0:12:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}与大气里的分子和原子相撞{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and colliding with the molecules and atoms in the atmosphere...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.46,0:12:14.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}引起它们发光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and causing them to glow.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.52,0:12:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以它根本不是恒星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So it's not a star at all...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.32,0:12:19.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}与恒星风马牛不相及{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}nothing even remotely similar to a star.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.06,0:12:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些闪闪发光的石子就是大家熟知的流星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}These glowing pebbles are better known as meteors.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.71,0:12:26.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大多数在焚毁在大气层{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Most burn up in the atmosphere.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.85,0:12:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有些 如果它们足够大的花{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Some, if they're large enough...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.11,0:12:29.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就可以让它一路穿过大气层{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}can make it all the way through the atmosphere...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.91,0:12:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}落到地球上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and drop to the Earth...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.53,0:12:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们就会发现叫做陨石的石头{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and we find a rock called a meteorite.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.59,0:12:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那其实是同一类现象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And that is really the same phenomenon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.08,0:12:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}构成流星的石头和尘埃粒子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The pebbles and dust particles that make up meteors...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.10,0:12:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是我们太阳系形成时残留的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}are leftovers from the formation of our solar system...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.55,0:12:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}主要是前几代恒星的碎片{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}mostly scattered debris from previous generations of stars.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.00,0:12:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其中许多还是来自小行星带{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Many of them also come from the asteroid belt.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.60,0:13:00.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在火星与木星之间{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Between Mars and Jupiter...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.90,0:13:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有一大堆石块漂浮在那里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there's a whole bunch of rocks floating around.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.91,0:13:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}偶尔 它们会互相撞击 破碎{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And, occasionally, they hit each other and shatter...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.40,0:13:10.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这些小颗粒在太阳系里飞来飞去{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and these little grains go flying around in the solar system...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.30,0:13:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其中有些最终会越过地球的大气层{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and some of them eventually intersect Earth's atmosphere.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.47,0:13:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在每年的某些时候{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}At certain times of the year...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.11,0:13:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有大量的流星接二连三划过天空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}a large number of meteors streak across the sky.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.96,0:13:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这种事件称为流星雨{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}These events are called meteor showers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.34,0:13:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们发生在地球穿过一串碎片{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They occur when the Earth passes through a trail of debris...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.99,0:13:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}彗星经过太阳时留下的大量冰粒与尘埃{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}bits of ice and grit left by a comet as it orbits the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.32,0:13:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你看到流星雨时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When you look at a meteor shower...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.04,0:13:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}流星似乎是从天上某一个点散发出来{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the meteors or shooting stars appear to emanate...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.65,0:13:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}光芒四射{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}from a single point in the sky, the radiant.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.42,0:13:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们从那里射出{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They radiate away from there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.77,0:13:48.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是 实际上 形成流星的小冰粒和石子{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But, really, the little bits of ice and rock...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.20,0:13:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}成堆穿行...{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that make up the meteors are traveling in a bundle...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.02,0:13:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}基本上是平行穿越太空的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}along essentially parallel paths through space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.88,0:13:58.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们并不是从一个点上散开的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They're not diverging from a single point.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.73,0:14:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们只是表现出散开状{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They only appear to be spreading apart...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.33,0:14:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为透视的缘故{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because of the perspective...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.22,0:14:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}事实上 你是在远距离看它们{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the fact that you're looking at them from a great distance...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.03,0:14:10.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们似乎是出自消失点{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and they seem to come from vanishing point.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.02,0:14:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你可以看到这个走廊里同样的情况{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You can see the exact same thing in this hallway.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.38,0:14:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}墙壁是相互平行的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The walls are parallel to one another...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.77,0:14:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}顶棚平行于地坪{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the ceiling is parallel to the floor...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.45,0:14:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}墙壁与地坪之间的交线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the lines of intersection between the floor and the wall...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.31,0:14:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}顶棚与墙壁的交线都是相互平行的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the ceiling and the wall are parallel to one another...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.71,0:14:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是它们似乎是汇聚于远处的走廊那一头{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but they all appear to converge far down the hallway there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.28,0:14:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们都出自消失点 是因为透视的缘故{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They come from a vanishing point because of the perspective.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.44,0:14:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果你以同样的方式回到流星上去{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And if you go back to the meteors...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.45,0:14:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}粒子都是相互平行的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in a similar way, the particles are all traveling parallel to one another...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.53,0:14:46.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是只表现出散射状{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but only appear to diverge from the radiant...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.13,0:14:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那是透视的缘故{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because of perspective.{\r}
